# CODEOWNERS for OpenSIN-AI/OpenSIN-overview
#
# This file is the first-line review gate for governance changes.
# Because OpenSIN-overview is the *governance index* (not a product repo),
# every file here has organisational consequences if changed wrongly:
#   - docs/ shapes how 205 repos are coordinated
#   - registry/ is consumed by external sites (my.opensin.ai marketplace)
#   - schemas/ is the contract every Team-SIN-* repo must satisfy
#   - scripts/ regenerates the registry automatically
#
# Format: <pattern>   <owners>
# Patterns match relative to the repo root; later rules override earlier ones.
# See https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ default
# Anything without a more specific rule: the OpenSIN-AI core team.
# NOTE: this team must exist in the GitHub org. If it doesn't, create it
#       via Org Settings → Teams → New team → "core" (or rename below).
*                                 @OpenSIN-AI/core

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ charter + boundaries (canon-locked)
# These six files are the canon-lock set. Per BOUNDARIES Rule 7 a change
# requires a §3.2 governance PR with at least one approver from a different
# team than the author. During launch week (T-4 → T+7) CTO sign-off is
# additionally required. CHANGELOG.md must record every entry.
/PRODUCT-VISION.md                @OpenSIN-AI/core
/STATE-OF-THE-UNION.md            @OpenSIN-AI/core
/BOUNDARIES.md                    @OpenSIN-AI/core
/GOVERNANCE.md                    @OpenSIN-AI/core
/LAUNCH-CHECKLIST.md              @OpenSIN-AI/core
/WORKFORCE.md                     @OpenSIN-AI/core
# Adjacent, near-canon docs (still core-only review)
/AGENTS.md                        @OpenSIN-AI/core
/START-HERE.md                    @OpenSIN-AI/core
/CHANGELOG.md                     @OpenSIN-AI/core

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ community-health surfaces
# These files are the org's public face on GitHub (community-standards score).
# Changes must be reviewed by core to keep the contract stable.
/SECURITY.md                      @OpenSIN-AI/core
/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md               @OpenSIN-AI/core
/SUPPORT.md                       @OpenSIN-AI/core
/CONTRIBUTING.md                  @OpenSIN-AI/core
/LICENSE                          @OpenSIN-AI/core
/.github/dependabot.yml           @OpenSIN-AI/core
/.github/FUNDING.yml              @OpenSIN-AI/core
/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/**        @OpenSIN-AI/core
/.github/pull_request_template.md @OpenSIN-AI/core

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ registry (external contract)
# These files feed external sites — changing them without review can
# break marketplace cards on my.opensin.ai.
/registry/**                      @OpenSIN-AI/core

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ schemas (contract)
# Schema changes are breaking changes for every Team-SIN-* repo.
/schemas/**                       @OpenSIN-AI/core

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ scripts (automation)
# Scripts regenerate the registry — breakage = dead dashboards.
# Two scripts are launch gates and need extra care:
#   - scripts/scan-secrets.sh  : breaks the secret-leak prevention if disabled
#   - scripts/check-workforce.js : breaks the workforce-drift gate if disabled
/scripts/**                       @OpenSIN-AI/core

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ CI + automation
/.github/workflows/**             @OpenSIN-AI/core
/governance/workflows-proposed/** @OpenSIN-AI/core
/.github/CODEOWNERS               @OpenSIN-AI/core
/.husky/**                        @OpenSIN-AI/core

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ team manifests (marketplace catalog)
# One Team-SIN-* manifest per marketplace bundle. Per Wave-4 Option A,
# the team that owns the bundle reviews its own manifest.
# Until those teams exist on GitHub, @OpenSIN-AI/core approves by default.
/templates/teams/**               @OpenSIN-AI/core

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ docs body
/docs/**                          @OpenSIN-AI/core

# ------------------------------------------------------------------ followups
# FOLLOWUPS.md is the single source of truth for open governance tickets.
# Only maintainers close tickets.
/docs/FOLLOWUPS.md                @OpenSIN-AI/core
